##Wuhan received two hard tasks: detection of all suspected cases, admission of all confirmed patients

Linkage of three medical, bridge capital, direct health

Wuhan districts are stepping up quarantine and testing of all people with fever in an effort to expose the disease and then move from a "battle of the bulge" to a "Battle of annihilation" 

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure / Fachen

Wen | CAIJING's special correspondent in Wuhan, Yan Qing, Wang Xiao

Editor | Wang Xiao

"Today's meeting is very important. We must not make any mistakes in understanding. If there are any problems, we will be held accountable. We are not bluffing. The general secretary's meeting the day before yesterday has already mentioned that if you can't do it right, you need to use a knife. " A spokesman said in a conference room on the 10th floor of the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission.

CAIJING reporter learned exclusively that in the morning of the same day, the Wuhan COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters held a meeting (hereinafter referred to as the headquarters meeting) , requiring all districts to within the next two days, until February 7 at the latest, complete nucleic acid tests for all suspected cases in Wuhan. In addition to the detection of suspected cases, the meeting also proposed to seek admission of all confirmed patients at 2400 hours on the evening of February 5.

These two tasks, is the superior to Wuhan put forward the hard requirements, but also the current Wuhan in the fight against the two major difficulties in the epidemic.

Wuhan nucleic acid testing of the highest capacity, has now reached 6000-8000 daily, outpatient capacity of 13000, if the various hospitals involved can be completed on schedule, will add nearly 7000 beds.

As of 17:00 on February 5, a total of 8,551 patients had been diagnosed, 362 had died and 373 had been cured. Between 00:00 and 24:00 on February 4, there were 3,156 new cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in Hubei Province, of which 1,967 were in Wuhan, accounting for 62.3% of the new cases in Hubei Province.

"CAIJING" reporters learned that Wuhan districts are stepping up the quarantine of all fever people, and all fever people testing, the aim is to let the epidemic all exposed, after reaching a high point, will show a steady downward trend, after the epidemic prevention and control will also be transferred from "hard-line battle" to "War of annihilation. ".

First task: Test All suspected cases in three days

"We have two or three days to expose all of Wuhan's problems. Looking at the current daily growth in Wuhan indicators, it has a lot to do with the current monitoring situation,"a spokesman for the command conference said.

On February 4, more than 1,000 nucleic acid tests and 13,000 fever clinic visits were conducted in Wuhan. At present, the main areas of Wuhan to carry out sampling, according to the information referred to at the headquarters meeting, the hospital suspected patients have all done testing.

More test kits are pouring into Hubei. "We have publicly pledged to donate 120,000 copies together with caring organizations and individuals, " a senior BGI official told Caijing. As of February 3, BGI has actually shipped 25,600 people to Wuhan and Hubei. Of these reagents, 9,500 were distributed in Wuhan and 16,100 in the non-wuhan region of Hubei.

The genetic information of the virus is stored in the nucleic acid, which indicates the characteristics of the virus, but also acts as an "identity card" , which can help researchers distinguish specific virus species.

There are two types of reagents, one is PCR, the other is sequencing. The main principle of PCR is to design another nucleic acid sequence which can match the virus identity information. In the vast sea of nucleic acids, like a probe, and a specific "identity" of the virus, to identify the recruit.

Sequencing is all about reading out all the nucleic acids. So the PCR method, which is fast enough to detect the presence of a virus, is more accurate, more comprehensive, and can even tell if the virus is mutating, but it's expensive and slow.

According to the above command meeting request, in two or three days to arrange for the detection of suspected patients in the community, quarantine staff in the quarantine points, and fever clinic transferred to the personnel.

The Order of detection was, first, highly suspicious, then the personnel at the isolation point, and then the personnel transferred from the fever clinic. In this order, all tests will be completed in no more than three days.

"The work is close to 21 hours a day. Now the amount of specimens is extremely large, and about 100 samples were tested yesterday, " said Tongji Medical College, a staff member at Tongji Hospital, affiliated to Tongji Medical College. Tongji hospital detection capacity has reached the daily nucleic acid detection capacity of 1000, every 4 hours about 180 batch detection.

At present, there are 45,000 test tubes needed for testing, which can meet the needs of testing.

"CAIJING" reporters learned that on February 2, Wuhan added a number of nucleic acid reagent testing institutions, respectively, Wuhan University People's Hospital, Wuhan No. 7 Hospital, Puai Hospital and so on.

Up to now, there are 31 institutions in Wuhan to carry out nucleic acid testing at the same time. The detection capacity of nucleic acid samples in a single day has increased from 200 in the initial stage to more than 4,000 in the recent past.

According to information released by the Hubei Provincial Health Commission on February 4, there are 40 institutions in Wuhan that can carry out COVID-19 nucleic acid testing, including the Hubei Provincial Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the Wuhan Center for Disease Control and Prevention, and 25 hospitals, with 13 third-party inspection agencies.

A doctor at a designated hospital in Wuhan told Caijing that he had seen patients with severe viral pneumonia on a CT scan of the lungs, both negative for nucleic acid and eventually positive. The positive rate of nucleic acid reagent in their hospital was 45% . To improve accuracy, the hospital will reconfirm the Shuangyang District test. February 5, the command meeting mentioned that the current Wuhan hospitals in the suspected patients, the second test has also been completed.

Second Task: admit all confirmed patients on the night of February 5

"All confirmed patients will be admitted before midnight tonight, " a spokesman for the command meeting said on the morning of February 5.

All the so-called admission, mainly seriously ill patients, by Wuhan Health Commission arrangements, received critical hospitals and designated hospitals; light patients, are arranged to enter the "shelter hospital. ".

Similar to the field mobile hospital, the "Shelter Hospital" is constructed by moving "Module House" , which includes medical shelter, technical support shelter, Ward Unit, Life Support Unit and transportation capacity.

The first "shelter hospitals" , located at the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center, the Wembley Arena and the Wuhan Living Room, have more than 3,000 beds for the treatment of patients with mild illness, that is, patients who test positive but have no symptoms or no obvious symptoms, and configuration of medical equipment and medical staff, patients for observation and treatment.

Of the three "shelter hospitals, " the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center will be operational on Feb. 5, and all three are scheduled to open on Feb. 6. It is reported that the "Cabin Hospital" admitted new patients with mild pneumonia, when the patient's symptoms once heavy, will be transferred to hospital in time.

At 10:00 a.m. on February 4, Caijing reporters saw at the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center that the first floor lobby was isolated by one or two-meter-high wooden boards into several independent areas of several hundred square meters, each individual area is equipped with more than 20 cots, a quilt folded in two, a mattress on the bed board, one side can be covered in the body, the quilt has electric blanket. Next to the single bed is a set of desks and chairs for personal use.

In the "Shelter Hospital" support medical team has the south-central hospital, the volunteer team has Xiangya Hospital.

According to the Hubei Daily News, as of 22:00 on the 4th, Wuhan has commandeered 11 venues to be converted into "shelter hospitals. ". Following the overnight construction of the above-mentioned three "shelter hospitals" , eight more were built in Wuhan on February 4, located in Wuhan International Expo Center, Tazihu Sports Center, Wuhan Sports Center, Shipai Ling Vocational High School, Wuhan Sports Center Stadium, Wuhan Guanggu Science and Technology Exhibition Center, Dahuashan Outdoor Sports Center, Huangpi No. 1 Middle School Sports Center, it can provide more than, beds.

If patients can not be admitted to the "shelter hospital" or designated hospitals, the sectors will arrange for temporary admission to private hospitals or other centralized isolation points. On February 3, a long queue formed outside a hotel in Wuhan Qiao estuary. They were feverish residents screened by the community and suspected to be infected with a new coronavirus.

A paramedic at the scene said that in two or three days, people living here will be tested for nucleic acid kits. The negative patients could leave directly; the patients with mild cases continued to be quarantined in the hotel and the patients with severe cases went to the hospital.

Anyone checking into a hotel needs to take their temperature first. A man with a temperature above 39 °C was dissuaded. "It's just an observation point, " explained one paramedic. "There's no treatment, there's no first aid. ".

A spokesman at the command meeting said that if any patients could not be admitted to the "shelter hospital" or designated hospitals, arrangements will be made by the districts to temporarily enter private hospitals in transition. In short, all confirmed patients will be placed in isolation, not at home.

(CAIJING reporter Sun Aimin contributed to this report.)
